h6. Expected Behaviour

Let's say we have the group "Grupo 1". After adding Group 1 to global permission *JIRA Administrators*, we add Group 1 to JIRA Users global permission and it works just fine.

h6. Actual Behaviour

When adding Grupo 1 to the global permission *JIRA Users*, after having added it to the group *JIRA Administrators*, the following error message is displayed and the group can't be added:

{quote}
The group 'Grupo 1' is not allowed to be added to the permission 'JIRA Users'
{quote}


h6. Workaround

Instead of adding the group to JIRA Administrators and then to JIRA Users, adding the group to JIRA Users and THEN JIRA Administrators works fine

*Update* : The behaviour above (workaround) is actually a bug, this is being tracked at JRA-37733.

