Users sometimes want to share the current results of a single gadget with specific people, without having to go through the effort of sharing both the underlying filter as well as the entire Dashboard on which the gadget is configured.

A simple "Share" option in the gadget menu (the drop-down menu at the right-hand side of the gadget title bar) would be ideal, where the gadget's current contents are exported as an HTML e-mail and then sent to the identified users with an optional message.

Sharing a single gadget today is quite painful, as copy-and-paste of the gadget is very dependent on the browser's selection capabilities (for copy), as well as the e-mail client's formatting capabilities (for paste).  The only alternative is to use a screen capture of the browser window, but this loses all of the links embedded in the gadget.

